<subSubSection id="6DE165012511FF92FF451486FD9BFBF3" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="1621" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619" type="description">
<paragraph id="2544368A2511FF91FF451486FD17FE84" blockId="4.[178,1085,1492,1602]" lastBlockId="5.[178,1085,218,299]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1620" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619">
Comment: 
<collectingCounty id="CC254E062511FF90FE911486FE1FFA45" box="[358,397,1492,1514]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619">The</collectingCounty>
original description is based on &quot;six examples&quot; from &quot; 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF8682511FF90FC201486FBABFA45" box="[983,1081,1492,1514]" country="Japan" name="Nagasaki" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619">Nagasaki</collectingRegion>
, Nikko, Miyanoshita&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="416A4B7B2511FF90FE6814A3FDB6F9A8" author="SHARP D" box="[415,548,1521,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619" pagination="463 - 476" refId="ref11439" refString="SHARP D. S. (1889): The Staphylinidae of Japan. - The Annals and Magazine of Natural History (6) 3: 28 - 44, 108 - 121, 249 - 267, 319 - 334, 406 - 419, 463 - 476." type="journal article" year="1889">SHARP 1889</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingMunicipality id="C520ACF02511FF90FDCD14A0FDDDF9A8" box="[570,591,1522,1543]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619">In</collectingMunicipality>
view of the usually restricted distributions of flightless 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D092511FF90FEE0175DFE70F98A" box="[279,482,1551,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="178FEA982511FF90FEE0175DFE1CF98A" box="[279,398,1551,1573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619">Lathrobium</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, there is little doubt that the type series is composed of at least three species. 
<location id="202460512511FF90FE8C177EFE24F9ED" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:AD52879C2511FF92FF4515F7FD9BFBF3:202460512511FF90FE8C177EFE24F9ED" box="[379,438,1580,1602]" county="The" municipality="In" name="Three" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619" stateProvince="Nagasaki">Three</location>
<typeStatus id="FA4088282511FF90FE49177FFD8BF9ED" box="[446,537,1581,1602]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619">syntypes</typeStatus>
, 
<specimenCount id="33FDFD032511FF90FDD1177FFD1DF9ED" box="[550,655,1580,1602]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1619" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
and a female, were located in the collections of the BMNH. One of the 
<specimenCount id="33FDFD032510FF91FDF71189FDFBFF5F" box="[512,617,218,240]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
from Miyanoshita is designated as the 
<typeStatus id="FA4088282510FF91FBF41188FF73FEA2" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specific identity of the female from Nikko is uncertain; it possibly belongs to the species described in the following section.
</paragraph>
<caption id="718466022510FF91FF451475FC6EFAFD" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303073" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5303073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303073/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620" startId="5.[178,218,1319,1339]" targetBox="[188,1054,317,1300]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="2544368A2510FF91FF451475FC6EFAFD" blockId="5.[178,1085,1319,1362]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">
<emphasis id="178FEA982510FF91FF451475FE90FA94" bold="true" box="[178,258,1319,1339]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">Figs 1-6</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D092510FF91FEE61475FD9DFA96" authority="SHARP" authorityName="Sharp, P. M. Hammond" authorityYear="1889" box="[273,527,1319,1339]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pollens">
<emphasis id="178FEA982510FF91FEE61475FE5AFA94" box="[273,456,1319,1339]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">Lathrobium pollens</emphasis>
SHARP
</taxonomicName>
, paralectotype: (
<emphasis id="178FEA982510FF91FD581475FD28FA94" bold="true" box="[687,698,1319,1339]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">1</emphasis>
) habitus; (
<emphasis id="178FEA982510FF91FCD31475FCBDFA94" bold="true" box="[804,815,1319,1339]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">2</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="178FEA982510FF91FC5E1475FC26FA94" bold="true" box="[937,948,1319,1339]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">3</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="178FEA982510FF91FF1A146CFF6AFAFD" bold="true" box="[237,248,1342,1362]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">4</emphasis>
) male sternite VII; (
<emphasis id="178FEA982510FF91FE45146CFE43FAFD" bold="true" box="[434,465,1342,1362]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">5-6</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="2544368A2510FF91FF451432FEC8FA61" blockId="5.[178,1085,1376,1486]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">
Redescription: Species of large size; body length 
<quantity id="E2039B6F2510FF91FCCF1432FC5DFAD9" box="[824,975,1376,1398]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.15" metricValueMin="1.05" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620" unit="mm" value="11.0" valueMax="11.5" valueMin="10.5">10.5-11.5 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="E2039B6F2510FF91FEE1142FFE02FA3C" box="[278,400,1405,1427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="4.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620" unit="mm" value="5.05" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="4.8">4.8-5.3 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2510FF91FDD9142FFDFEFA3C" box="[558,620,1405,1427]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1319,1339]" captionTargetBox="[188,1054,317,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1085,317,1312]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-6: Lathrobium pollens SHARP, paralectotype: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) male sternite VII; (5-6) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303073/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Coloration: forebody brown to dark-brown; abdomen dark-brown to blackish-brown; legs reddish to dark-reddish with paler tarsi; antennae brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2510FF92FF45148FFDD2FE84" blockId="5.[178,1085,1501,1582]" lastBlockId="6.[178,1086,218,299]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="1621" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">
Head (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2510FF91FF0F148FFEA4FA5C" box="[248,310,1501,1523]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1319,1339]" captionTargetBox="[188,1054,317,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1085,317,1312]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-6: Lathrobium pollens SHARP, paralectotype: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) male sternite VII; (5-6) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303073/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1620">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) large and transverse, 1.12-1.13 times as broad as long, somewhat dilated behind eyes, and with convex lateral margins in dorsal view; punctation relatively fine and dense, somewhat sparser in median dorsal portion and on frons; interstices with fine and rather shallow microreticulation. Eyes weakly convex, composed of&gt; 50 fine ommatidia, and relatively small, approximately one third as long as postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna 
<quantity id="E2039B6F2513FF92FE671047FD97FE84" box="[400,517,277,299]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.7">2.7-2.8 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2513FF92FF451069FBBEFE24" blockId="6.[178,1086,314,395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2513FF92FEDF1068FEFAFEFF" box="[296,360,314,336]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1319,1339]" captionTargetBox="[188,1054,317,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1085,317,1312]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-6: Lathrobium pollens SHARP, paralectotype: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) male sternite VII; (5-6) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303073/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) broad, approximately 1.15 times as long as broad and as broad as head, widest near anterior angles and distinctly tapering posteriad; punctation similar to that of head; interstices without microsculpture; impunctate median band rather narrow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2513FF92FF4510C8FEC7FE44" blockId="6.[178,1086,410,491]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2513FF92FEF610C8FED2FE1F" box="[257,320,410,432]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1319,1339]" captionTargetBox="[188,1054,317,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1085,317,1312]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-6: Lathrobium pollens SHARP, paralectotype: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) male sternite VII; (5-6) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303073/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) approximately 0.55 times as long as pronotum; punctation more or less defined, moderately dense, somewhat finer than that of pronotum. Hind wings completely reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2513FF92FF4510A8FE31FDE5" blockId="6.[178,1085,506,586]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">Abdomen distinctly broader than elytra; punctation fine and dense, that of tergites VII and VIII slightly less dense than that of anterior tergites; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2513FF92FF301309FD65FC3B" blockId="6.[178,1086,602,916]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">
: protarsomeres I-IV strongly dilated; tergite VIII with very weakly concave to nearly truncate posterior margin; sternites III-VI unmodified; sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2513FF92FC7E1325FC5EFD22" box="[905,972,631,653]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1319,1339]" captionTargetBox="[188,1054,317,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1085,317,1312]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-6: Lathrobium pollens SHARP, paralectotype: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) male sternite VII; (5-6) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303073/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) distinctly transverse, posteriorly with distinct median impression, posterior margin with distinct and broad concavity in the middle, lateral margins of this concavity furnished with dense and long dark setae; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2513FF92FDE6139DFDDCFD4A" box="[529,590,719,741]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1319,1339]" captionTargetBox="[188,1054,317,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1085,317,1312]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-6: Lathrobium pollens SHARP, paralectotype: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) male sternite VII; (5-6) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303073/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad, posterior excision of nearly semi-circular shape, margin of this excision furnished with dense dark setae laterally, posterior margin on either side of posterior excision acutely produced; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="BDC02A0F2513FF92FED71275FEE8FC92" box="[288,378,807,829]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="5.[178,218,1319,1339]" captionTargetBox="[188,1054,317,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-1@5.[178,1085,317,1312]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1-6: Lathrobium pollens SHARP, paralectotype: (1) habitus; (2) forebody; (3) male sternite VIII; (4) male sternite VII; (5-6) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303073/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">Figs 5-6</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="E2039B6F2513FF92FE7B1275FD94FC93" box="[396,518,807,829]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.6">2.6-2.7 mm</quantity>
long and symmetric; ventral process slender, weakly curved in lateral view and apically acute, ventrally with pair of long carinae; dorsal plate very long, slender, lamellate, and apically acute, basal portion distinctly longer than apical portion; internal sac without sclerotized structures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2513FF92FF3012F7FEA8FC15" blockId="6.[199,314,932,954]" box="[199,314,932,954]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">: unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2513FF92FF45129BFD52FBB5" blockId="6.[178,1085,969,1050]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">Comparative notes: This species is characterized particularly by the large and broad body, as well as by the male sexual characters, above all the shape of the conspicuously long ventral process of the aedeagus.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2544368A2513FF92FF45157BFD9BFBF3" blockId="6.[178,1085,1065,1116]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">
Distribution: The 
<typeStatus id="FA4088282513FF92FE271578FE6EFB90" box="[464,508,1066,1087]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">type</typeStatus>
locality [
<geoCoordinate id="40CF504D2513FF92FDAB157BFD26FB90" box="[604,692,1065,1087]" degrees="35" direction="north" minutes="14" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621" precision="925" value="35.233334">35°14'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="40CF504D2513FF92FD49157BFC8CFB90" box="[702,798,1065,1087]" degrees="139" direction="east" minutes="03" orientation="longitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621" precision="925" value="139.05">139°03'E</geoCoordinate>
] is situated in the southwest of 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF8682513FF92FF3A1515FE38FBF3" box="[205,426,1094,1116]" country="Japan" name="Kanagawa" pageId="6" pageNumber="1621">Kanagawa Prefecture</collectingRegion>
, Honshu.
</paragraph>
